snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Ammar,
I really hope you are doing good at the moment !!
I’ve discovered your YouTube channel almost a month ago and since then I’ve been watching every single video from your day one until now. And believe me, I’m already out of my confort zone by just sending you this message. 

Indeed, I’ve been watching YouTube videos since so many years and I absolutely love it as I think this is the most positive social media thanks to incredible inspiring people like you. But I also think that you, youtubers, receive so many message that it is hopeless for you to see this. However, throughout your videos, you made the point of doing what we really want so there it is. 

I’ve been dealing with mental health issues pretty much my entiere life whether it was me or my beloved one. I think that mental health disorders are such a big taboo and a huge source of shame. I’ve myself been with depression and I’m so ashamed about it that it has causes incredible lack of self esteem. My friends don’t catch my signals and my family has suffer so much from other mental illness that I can bother them with mine. 

You have inspired me so much about many things that I just wanted to know if it could be possible to have a simple FaceTime call to talk about how we should/can deal with depression and what can help us. I know it sounds like a crazy request but I feel like you have many advice to give or maybe I would be able to give you some (we never know 😉). 

I’m so ready to spread the seek discomfort motto around me (and I have already started) but my self esteem and self confiance are preventing me from so many things... I want it to stop now and I truly think you can help me.

Meanwhile, I will be doing one R.A.K a day getting hope to have a small talk with you. 

Best wishes for the end of year, 
Julie from France.
